rComments: Good prof-unlike my mates, I did not find him cocky. Enjoyed the class.

Course was a series of presentations by professionals from the field about ethics/princaples in CSI practice, organized by Probert. Probert constantly interrupted the presentations by making pointless comments, or fiddling with equipment for no other reason than to bring attention to himself. Unprofessional. Good at remembering student names though

Good hearted, Passionate about his field and lovers to share it with students. Is totally disorganized. Lectures notes in slide format is  bundle of disorganized and repetitive material. Overall structure of his course needs revamping. If at least he had his material organized, that would help.
